Liverpool will play Real Madrid in the UEFA Champions League final in Kiev on 26 May after they survived Roma scare at the Olympic Stadium in Rome, winning 7-6 aggregate. Roma won on the night, scoring two goals in five minutes to raise the hope of a spectacular comeback having lost the first leg 2-5. But there was no second miracle in Rome, like it happened in the quarter finals when Roma erased Barcelona’s 4-1 advantage. Details later… 